Defendant William E Bishop in court with Attorney James T Moczydlowski.  Michele W. Hulgaard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  State gives sentencing recommendation and also states request for restitution.  Attorney Moczydlowski makes statements regarding sentencing and statements regarding restitution.  Case proceeds to restitution hearing.  State's exhibit #1 marked.  John J. is sworn-in and testifies.  Cross-examination by Attorney Moczydlowski. Re-direct by the state.  Re-cross by Attorney Moczydlowski.  State's exhibit #1 is offered and received.  Defendant William Bishop is sworn-in and testifies.  Cross-examination by the state.  Closing statements by the state.  Closing statements by Attorney Moczydlowski.  Court orders restitution to be paid by Defendant in the amount of $1,883.88 (break down listed below).  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:   IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

9 MONTHS HUBER                *Consecutive to 15CF4293 (Milw. Co case)

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS    *CONCURRENT*     **transfer allowed to Milwaukee County**
 
CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribed/sign releases
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with:  John J. or business listed in criminal complaint 
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 

RESTITUTION:  $150.00 to Pawn America (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)
                          $813.88 to Puroclean (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)
                          $880.00 to Puroclean (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)
                            $40.00 ($300.00 for IICRC minus $260.00 for withheld wages to Defendant) (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)


COSTS:  $278.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation)

CONDITION TIME:  60 DAYS, Non-working hours with standard release conditions to commence 8/10/16 by 5:00 p.m.(transfer allowed to Milwaukee County but NO ELECTRONIC MONITORING) - LAST 30 DAYS STAYED - to be used at agent's discretion

***Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and restitution paid in full and no new criminal law violations.***
